# CS 1410/1415: Object Oriented Programming & Lab 
Taken Spring 2022
Professor: Jonathan Allen

This course introduced students to the principles and practice of object-oriented programming using C# as the language of focus. Principles covered included encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism. Topics also covered included exception handling, basic data structures, and recursion.

Course syllabi:
